content:
When using Knowledge in Salesforce Classic, agents can send an article's content embedded in the body of the email or social post. Create a communication channel mapping to choose which article fields are included for each article type.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience (not available in all orgs) and Unlimited Edition with Service Cloud.

To administer Salesforce Knowledge and create, edit, and delete page layouts:

Customize Application

AND

Manage Salesforce Knowledge


To send article content in emails in Classic Knowledge:

Edit on cases AND read on Knowledge articles


To send internal content in emails in Classic Knowledge:

Enable Share internal Knowledge articles externally

AND

Enable Attaching articles inline

Email-to-case must be enabled. An HTML Body or Text field must be in the SendEmail layout.

From Setup, enter Knowledge Article Types and select it. Click New or Edit. Enter a label and name. Add Email to the Selected Channels list. Add the fields to include in the body of an email. Note that certain fields are not supported.

Agents can insert article content into the body of an email by selecting Email article with HTML in the action dropdown. When an article has been emailed, an envelope icon appears to the left of the title.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To administer Salesforce Knowledge... 

FROM THE OBJECT MANAGEMENT SETTINGS FOR CASES...

For a layout in the Case Page Layouts section, click Edit, and then click Feed View in the page layout editor.

For a layout in the Page Layouts for Case Feed Users section, click  and choose Edit feed view. (This section appears only for organizations created before Spring '14.)

If you've already opted to use the advanced page layout editor... 

Under Articles Tool Settings, select Enable attaching articles inline.
(Optional) Under Administrative Permissions, select Share internal Knowledge articles, externally.

Click Save.

From Setup, enter Knowledge Article Types in the Quick Find box, then select Knowledge Article Types. Click the label or name of the article type you want to share via email.
title: Configuring Article Insertion in Case Publishers
